## Primordial Soup — AI Agent Context

All project rules, coding conventions, and architecture decisions are
in `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root. Read it before making changes.

### Key references

- **Project rules and coding style:** `CLAUDE.md`
- **Design corpus (authoritative):** `docs/design/index.md`
  has reading order; `docs/design/core_simulator.md`,
  `docs/design/interfaces.md`, `docs/design/governance.md`, and
  `docs/design/initiative_model.md` are the technical authority.
- **Open issues:** `docs/implementation/open_implementation_issues.md`
- **Calibration plan:** `docs/implementation/calibration_plan.md`

### Critical rules

- Python 3.12+, `from __future__ import annotations` in every module.
- `frozen=True` on all dataclasses.
- `logging` only, never `print`.
- Engine never branches on initiative labels.
- Latent `q` and `true_duration_ticks` never visible to governance.
- Per-initiative CRN streams (no global RNG).
- All iteration in stable `id` order.
- Design corpus is frozen — do not change model semantics.

### Source layout

- `src/primordial_soup/` — simulation package
- `tests/` — pytest tests
- `docs/design/` — frozen design corpus
- `docs/implementation/` — implementation state files
